  "aboutBody": [
    "Session Climbing is a state-of-the-art indoor climbing, yoga, and fitness center in Santa Rosa, founded by world-class climbers Kevin Jorgeson, who free-climbed the Dawn Wall of El Capitan, and Mike Shaffer. Named Best North Bay Recreation Project, the 23,578-square-foot facility opened in 2022 with extensive bouldering terrain and rope walls reaching up to 50 feet.",
    "Above the climbing floor sit a 1,300-square-foot yoga studio with an open-air balcony looking out to Taylor Mountain and a communal cafe lounge. With classes, coaching, and robust youth camps and teams, Session welcomes everyone from first-time climbers to seasoned athletes, built on the idea that time well spent leads to a life well lived."
